# Badge

A badge is used to draw attention to certain information, status, or items that may require the customers' attention. Use badges when communicating status or drawing attention to items, such as:

- Status within tables, tabs, or lists
- Errors or warnings regarding data we have or information being entered
- New features or items that have been introduced or in limited release

Badges themselves are not interactive but may be included in interactive components.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/badge
```

```tsx
import { Badge } from '@ids-ts/badge';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | This prop is used for testing purposes |
| `label` | `React.ReactNode` | No | A label to show next to the badge |
| `shape` | `Shape` | No | The layout of the status badge. Defaults to rectangular for text |
| `status` | `Status` | No | - |
| `value` | `React.ReactNode` | No | Optional value (children can also be used) |
| `position` | `'left' | 'right' | 'center'` | No | Position of the badge relative to its parent. Default is center. |
| `priority` | `Priority` | No | - |
| `icon` | `React.FunctionComponent<IconProps>` | No | - |
| `capitalization` | `Capitalization` | No | - |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface BadgeProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /** This prop is used for testing purposes */
  automationId?: string;
  /** Surfaces a label to assistive technology (critical when no `label` is supplied) */
  'aria-label'?: string;
  /** A label to show next to the badge  */
  label?: React.ReactNode;
  /** The layout of the status badge. Defaults to rectangular for text */
  shape?: Shape;
  /**
   * The status for the badge to display
   *
   * @default 'info'
   */
  status?: Status;
  /** Optional value (children can also be used) */
  value?: React.ReactNode;
  /** Position of the badge relative to its parent. Default is center. */
  position?: 'left' | 'right' | 'center';
  /**
   * How the background prioritizes the button.
   * Badge priority - primary, secondary.
   *
   * @default primary
   */
  priority?: Priority;
  /**
   * An optional icon component to display next to the badge.
   * This icon is used when the badge has a secondary priority and sentence capitalization.
   */
  icon?: React.FunctionComponent<IconProps>;
  /**
   * Sentence case of the badge's text.
   * Badge capitalization - caps, sentence.
   *
   * @default caps
   */
  capitalization?: Capitalization;
}

export type Shape = 'round';

export type Status = 'info' | 'success' | 'pending' | 'warning' | 'error' | 'draft' | 'new' | 'beta';

export type Priority = 'primary' | 'secondary';

export type Capitalization = 'caps' | 'sentence';
```

</details>

## Token Usage

### Color

**container-feedback** — Feedback container colors (info, success, warning, error)

**text** — Primary and secondary text colors
- `--color-text-accent`
- `--color-text-complementary`
- `--color-text-disabled`

### Space

**container** — Container padding
- `--space-container-padding-large`
- `--space-container-padding-medium`
- `--space-container-padding-small`

### Radius

**radius** — Border radius
- `--radius-0`
- `--radius-10`
- `--radius-20`

### Font

**font** — Font family, size, weight, and line height
- `--font-size-12`
- `--font-size-14`
- `--font-size-16`

## Usage Patterns

### Showcase

```tsx
() => (
  <div
    style={{
      display: 'flex',
      flexDirection: 'column',
      gap: '20px'
    }}
  >
    <div>
      <H3>Example of a Text Badge</H3>
      <div
        style={{
          display: 'flex',
          flexDirection: 'column',
          alignItems: 'flex-start'
        }}
      >
        <B3 as="p">A text badge contains a few words to indicate status.</B3>
        <Badge status="success">Approved</Badge>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <H3>Example of an Icon Badge</H3>
      <div
        style={{
          display: 'flex',
          flexDirection: 'column',
          alignItems: 'flex-start'
        }}
      >
        <B3 as="p">
          Icon badges are used to indicate status with an icon. There are
          multiple icons exported from the Badge package that are recommended
          for use with icon badges. Here&apos;s an example with the success icon
          badge.
        </B3>
        <Badge shape="round" status="success">
          <SuccessBadgeIcon />
        </Badge>
        <br />
        <Badge shape="round" status="success" label="Approved">
          <SuccessBadgeIcon />
        </Badge>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <H3>Example of a Numeric Badge</H3>
      <div
        style={{
          display: 'flex',
          flexDirection: 'column',
          alignItems: 'flex-start',
          gap: '8px'
        }}
      >
        <B3 as="p">
          A badge can display a number in the container. A number badge always
          has a neutral status. If the number is higher than the max limit, a +
          will appear next to the number inside the container. (Example: 99+).
        </B3>
        <NumericBadge quantity={42} />
        <NumericBadge quantity={1000} />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <H3>Example of a Dot Badge</H3>
      <div
        style={{
          display: 'flex',
          flexDirection: 'column',
          alignItems: 'flex-start'
        }}
      >
        <B3 as="p">
          Dot badges are recommended to be used as an empty state for Numeric
          Badges.
        </B3>
// ...
